README 
	for GLeap_Frog Package
	Last edited on 05/24/2021 -- GAREEVES

PIPELINE OVERVIEW
	This package allows for the interconversion of and coordinate feature data from genomes
	used to generate a whole genome multi-alignment. 

HARDWARE SPECIFICATIONS	
	The pipeline is designed to work on MacOS architecture

TEST CASE
	Test case data will be made available in future updates

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------	
DIRECTORY SETUP					|
	./GLeap_Frog/				| -- The directory for the pipeline
		/Alt_Species/			| -- For Alternative species directories
			/Species1/		| -- Alternative Species One coordinate/feature file
			/....			| 
			/SpeicesN/		| -- Alternative Species N coordinate/feature file
		/Ref_Species/			| -- Reference Species coordinate/feature file
		/MAFs/				| -- For pairwise and multi-alignment MAF files
		/scripts/			| -- For scripts that run pipeline
						|
						|
REQUIRED PACKAGES				|
	bedtools					| -- https://bedtools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/content/installation.html
	    sort					|
	    intersect				|
						|
						|
REQUIRED FILES					|
	INPUT DATA				| -> Tabular Coordinate/Features files
		Alt_Species.txt			| 
		Ref_Species.txt			| -> MAF format alignment files
		Ref_Alt.maf			|
		Ref_All_Alt.maf			|
						|
	SCRIPTS					|-> placed in ~/WGA/Scripts/
		Make_Frog.py			| -- Cleans Reference Species Coordinate
		Gleap.py				| -- Converts Alternative Species Coordinates to Reference
		Second_Hop.py			| -- Evaluate Coordinate Overlap between Alternative and Reference
						|    Used on data generated by GLeap.py
		Plot_PCAs.R			| -- Use to visualize overlapping metadata from Second_Hop.py
						|
						|	
PRE-RUNNING INSTRUCTIONS				|
	Path update				| add the paths to all packages to your .bashrc/.bash_profile
						|
	Script updates				|
		Make_Frog.py			| Runs with no changes
		GLeap.py				| OPTIONAL: Change Reference suffix on line 272 for cleaner output naming
		Second_Hop.py			| Set Percentage Overlap Requirement on line 32
						| Set Up included Species Dictionaries on lines 34-36
						| Set Number of Data files per species on line 37
						| Adjust output headers on lines 40-54
						| Set Input file prefix on line 67
						|
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
		